main event: A civilian reported a sighting of a circular, blinking object on February 7, 1969.
interesting points: The object was the size of a volleyball and appeared to be at an altitude of 1500 ft. or less.,The sighting lasted for about 3 minutes.,The object was moving northwest towards the Buffalo area.,The witness was not able to take a picture since they were driving.,The sighting occurred approximately 11 miles northwest of Auburn, New York.
